04/03/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The fight against the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) is not over and if necessary, new operations may follow, the chief of the General Staff, General Yasar Buyukanit, said on Monday (March 3rd).
Turkey conducted ground attacks against PKK bases in northern Iraq between February 21st and February 28th.
At a press conference Monday, Buyukanit described the operation as "one of the most significant in the history of the Turkish armed forces".
He said the troops faced difficult winter weather, moved on foot without transport vehicles, and fought several battles at night."The goals of the operation was achieved," he said.
(Radikal, Hurriyet, Sabah, Zaman - 04/03/08;
ITAR-TASS, RIA Novosti, CNN Turk, Milliyet - 03/03/08)
